FBIS3-39210 "drweu030_b_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-030 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Feb 1994 Belgium Claes Said `Very Happy' With NATO Ultimatum LD1002152894 Brussels Radio Vlaanderen International in English 1400 GMT 10 Feb 94 LD1002152894 Brussels Radio Vlaanderen International Language: English Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] Belgian Foreign Affairs Minister Willy Claes is very happy with the NATO ultimatum reached last Wednesday [9 February]. NATO has given the Bosnian Serbs 10 days to lift the siege of Sarajevo. According to the minister, the Serbs now have no other choice than to retreat from their positions around the city by 21 February. Also Belgium is prepared to cooperate with possible air strikes, but Minister Claes says he thinks that our country will in the first place be asked to offer logistics support. [passage omitted] Belgian Foreign Affairs Minister Willy Claes says he is not worried about the strong opposition of the Russians. He says that it is Moscow that is making a mistake, not NATO.
